%N A394011 Decimal expansion of Product_{p prime} (1-1/p)^2 * (1 + Sum_{k >= 0} (2^k + 1)/p^(2^k)).
%C A394011 The asymptotic probability that the product of two positive integers selected independently at random is an exponentially 2^n number (A138302).
%e A394011 0.683988141437805930435510053776353193243930422806695...
%o A394011 (PARI) c(m) = prodeulerrat((1-1/p)^2 * (1 + sum(k = 0, m, (2^k+1)/p^(2^k))));
%o A394011 {my(c1 = 0, c2 = 1, m = 1); while(c2 != c1, c1 = c2; c2 = c(m); m++); c2}
%Y A394011 Cf. A138302, A065473 (squarefree analog), A394004 (exponentially odd analog), A394008 (cubefree analog).
%K A394011 nonn,cons
%O A394011 0,1
